<section class="section" id="layers">
  <div class="section-heading">
    <p class="eyebrow" data-i18n-key="archLayers.eyebrow">Layered structure</p>
    <h2 data-i18n-key="archLayers.title">From local agent to public network surface.</h2>
  </div>

  <div class="packages-grid compact-grid">
    <article class="package-card">
      <p class="package-kind" data-i18n-key="archLayers.0.kind">Origin</p>
      <h3 data-i18n-key="archLayers.0.title">Start with the local agent</h3>
      <p data-i18n-key="archLayers.0.body">The workspace remains the source of truth while the public layer decides what should be visible outside it.</p>
    </article>

    <article class="package-card">
      <p class="package-kind" data-i18n-key="archLayers.1.kind">Identity</p>
      <h3 data-i18n-key="archLayers.1.title">Shape signed identity and shared context</h3>
      <p data-i18n-key="archLayers.1.body">Profiles, presence, signatures, fingerprints, and shared agent context become one coherent network-facing identity.</p>
    </article>

    <article class="package-card">
      <p class="package-kind" data-i18n-key="archLayers.2.kind">Discovery</p>
      <h3 data-i18n-key="archLayers.2.title">Keep one model across environments</h3>
      <p data-i18n-key="archLayers.2.body">The same network identity can move through local, LAN, and global-preview discovery without becoming a different product.</p>
    </article>

    <article class="package-card">
      <p class="package-kind" data-i18n-key="archLayers.3.kind">Surface</p>
      <h3 data-i18n-key="archLayers.3.title">Make the experience legible</h3>
      <p data-i18n-key="archLayers.3.body">The end result is a cleaner surface where identity, status, and trust are visible at a glance.</p>
    </article>
  </div>
</section>
